SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 72
BY SENATOR SEABAUGH
COMMENDATIONS. Commends Todd McClure on being inducted into the 2026 class of
the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend Todd McClure on being inducted into the 2026 class of the Louisiana Sports
3 Hall of Fame.
4 WHEREAS, each year the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame in Natchitoches, Louisiana,
5 collaborates with the Louisiana Sports Writers Association in selecting a limited number of
6 sports figures who embody the character, skill, talent, and accomplishment worthy of being
7 named to the Hall of Fame; and
8 WHEREAS, the 2026 Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame Induction Class includes Todd
9 McClure; and
10 WHEREAS, Todd McClure, a native of Baton Rouge, distinguished himself as an
11 exceptional athlete, leader, and competitor whose accomplishments on the football field
12 brought pride to his hometown and the state of Louisiana; and
13 WHEREAS, McClure first rose to prominence as a standout three-sport athlete at
14 Central High School, where he earned All-State honors in football, baseball and contributed
15 to a basketball team that reached the state finals; and
16 WHEREAS, he continued his athletic career at Louisiana State University, where he
17 played four seasons for the LSU Tigers football and started 37 games at center, establishing
18 himself as one of the premier offensive linemen in the Southeastern Conference; and
